str2: If. A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: From a compound of therion and machomai; to be a beast-fighter, i.e. to encounter.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
Ephesus, a coast city, capital of the Roman province Asia. Probably of foreign origin; Ephesus, a city of Asia Minor.
A primary particle; down, in varied relations (genitive, dative or accusative) with which it is joined).
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Neuter Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.
Advantage, gain, profit, help. From ophello; gain.
If. A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.
(a) adj: dead, lifeless, subject to death, mortal, (b) noun: a dead body, a corpse. From an apparently primary nekus; dead.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Plural
str2: (a) I wake, arouse, (b) I raise up. Probably akin to the base of agora; to waken, i.e. Rouse.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 1st Person Plural
Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 1st Person Plural
str2: To drink, imbibe. A prolonged form of pio, which poo occurs only as an alternate in certain tenses; to imbibe.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.
Tomorrow. From a derivative of the same as aer; properly, fresh, i.e. to-morrow.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 1st Person Plural
str2: To be dying, be about to die, wither, decay. From apo and thnesko; to die off.
